   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>Year 2 of Lucius Septimius Severus Pertinax Augustus. I, Ammonios son of Onnophris and my colleagues, sitologoi of the villages of Lagis and of Trikomia, we have had meaasured to us from the produce of the same year of wheat by smoothed public measure to the account of Sarapion son of Harpalos from Tebtynis for the tax on lessees of state land eleven and a half artabai of wheat, total 11 1/2 artabai of wheat. I, Kastor, scribe of the sitologoi, wrote it.</ab>
         </div>
